[2025-09-20T20:05:27.958Z] [INFO] Received stdin input: {"session_id":"90241b75-5090-4df7-989a-d94b8d758310","transcript_path":"C:\\Users\\tamtr\\.claude\\projects\\D--sources-demo-eye-rest\\90241b75-5090-4df7-989a-d94b8d758310.jsonl","cwd":"D:\\sources\\demo\\eye-rest","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","hook_event_name":"PostToolUse","tool_name":"WebSearch","tool_input":{"query":"System.Media.SystemSounds Play method not working windows WPF .NET 8"},"tool_response":{"query":"System.Media.SystemSounds Play method not working windows WPF .NET 8","results":["I'll search for information about the System.Media.SystemSounds Play method issue in Windows WPF .NET 8.",{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01Fo5SoWwu6C6yE6ogw9wiDB","content":[{"title":"SystemSound.Play Method (System.Media) | Microsoft Learn","url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.media.systemsound.play?view=windowsdesktop-9.0"},{"title":"SoundPlayer.Play Method (System.Media) | Microsoft Learn","url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.media.soundplayer.play?view=windowsdesktop-9.0"},{"title":"c# - SystemSounds Play not working - Stack Overflow","url":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/343790/systemsounds-play-not-working"},{"title":"c# - Playing Windows System Sounds with System.Media.SoundPlayer - Stack Overflow","url":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/22123899/playing-windows-system-sounds-with-system-media-soundplayer"},{"title":"SoundPlayer Class (System.Media) | Microsoft Learn","url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.media.soundplayer?view=windowsdesktop-9.0"},{"title":"c# - How to play a sound file? - Stack Overflow","url":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/22745278/how-to-play-a-sound-file"},{"title":"c# - WPF (system)sounds don't work - Stack Overflow","url":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/7153399/wpf-systemsounds-dont-work"},{"title":"Playing audio - The complete WPF tutorial","url":"https://wpf-tutorial.com/audio-video/playing-audio/"},{"title":"SystemSounds Class (System.Media) | Microsoft Learn","url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.media.systemsounds?view=windowsdesktop-9.0&viewFallbackFrom=net-8.0"},{"title":"How to: Play a System Sound from a Windows Form - Windows Forms .NET Framework | Microsoft Learn","url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/desktop/winforms/controls/how-to-play-a-system-sound-from-a-windows-form?view=netframeworkdesktop-4.8"}]},"Based on the search results, here are the key findings about System.Media.SystemSounds Play method issues in Windows WPF .NET 8:\n\n## Common Issues and Solutions\n\n### 1. **System Sound Not Playing - Requires Restart**\nSome users report that SystemSounds.Play() stops working on Windows devices, and the issue is often resolved by simply restarting the device. Both System.Media.SystemSounds.Beep.Play() and System.Console.Beep() may stop working, but after a reboot they work again.\n\n### 2. **How SystemSounds Works Internally**\nSystemSounds returns a SystemSound instance initialized with the type (e.g. 0x40 for Asterisk) which is then passed to the Win32 MessageBeep method. The method is imported as a DllImport from \"user32.dll\", but the bool return isn't preserved, though exceptions are not swallowed so you should get any if thrown.\n\n### 3. **Basic SystemSounds Usage**\nThe Play method plays the sound asynchronously. The SystemSounds class provides methods for retrieving sounds associated with operating system sound-event types that can be configured in Windows Control Panel, including Asterisk, Beep, Exclamation, Hand and Question events, with each property returning a SystemSound that can be used to play the sound.\n\n### 4. **Alternative Approaches for WPF**\nWPF has a SoundPlayer class for WAV format, but it's not terribly useful due to WAV's uncompressed nature. Instead, MediaPlayer and MediaElement classes are recommended for playing MP3 files, though SystemSounds class remains the simplest option.\n\n### 5. **Event Handler Issues**\nIn WPF applications, ensure that event handlers are properly hooked up in the XAML file, such as connecting Button's Click event to the handler method.\n\n## Recommendations:\n1. **Try restarting Windows** if SystemSounds suddenly stops working\n2. **Check Windows Sound settings** in Control Panel to ensure system sounds are configured\n3. **Verify event handlers** are properly connected if using in button click events\n4. **Consider MediaPlayer class** for more complex audio requirements beyond system sounds\n5. **Use proper namespace**: Include `System.Media` namespace for SystemSounds functionality\n\nThe issue appears to be more related to Windows system configuration or temporary system state rather than a .NET 8 specific problem, as the API itself remains consistent across .NET versions."],"durationSeconds":25.323974400000008}}
