[2025-09-20T20:16:19.110Z] [INFO] Received stdin input: {"session_id":"90241b75-5090-4df7-989a-d94b8d758310","transcript_path":"C:\\Users\\tamtr\\.claude\\projects\\D--sources-demo-eye-rest\\90241b75-5090-4df7-989a-d94b8d758310.jsonl","cwd":"D:\\sources\\demo\\eye-rest","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","hook_event_name":"PostToolUse","tool_name":"WebSearch","tool_input":{"query":"C# WPF SystemSounds not playing Windows 11 10 audio muted system sounds disabled troubleshoot"},"tool_response":{"query":"C# WPF SystemSounds not playing Windows 11 10 audio muted system sounds disabled troubleshoot","results":["I'll search for information about troubleshooting SystemSounds not playing in C# WPF applications on Windows 11/10, including issues with muted audio and disabled system sounds.",{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01KgSSdBCwPRQ1qZZ4RGWYsc","content":[{"title":"Fix sound or audio problems in Windows - Microsoft Support","url":"https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/fix-sound-or-audio-problems-in-windows-73025246-b61c-40fb-671a-2535c7cd56c8"},{"title":"Windows 10 System Sounds Not Playing Audio | Windows 11 Forum","url":"https://www.elevenforum.com/t/windows-10-system-sounds-not-playing-audio.16254/"},{"title":"c# - WPF (system)sounds don't work - Stack Overflow","url":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/7153399/wpf-systemsounds-dont-work"},{"title":"Windows 10 Not Playing System Sounds. All Other Sounds Are Okay. Solved - Windows 10 Forums","url":"https://www.tenforums.com/sound-audio/126126-windows-10-not-playing-system-sounds-all-other-sounds-okay.html"},{"title":"Windows 10 System Sound is on mute but it still plays","url":"https://answers.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/forum/all/windows-10-system-sound-is-on-mute-but-it-still/4c1a124f-5554-48aa-9970-a0a1b0207aa4"},{"title":"audio - Windows 10 Volume Mixer fails to keep System Sounds muted over Remote Desktop Connection - Super User","url":"https://superuser.com/questions/1119689/windows-10-volume-mixer-fails-to-keep-system-sounds-muted-over-remote-desktop-co"},{"title":"Playing audio - The complete WPF tutorial","url":"https://wpf-tutorial.com/audio-video/playing-audio/"},{"title":"How to Fix No Sound on Windows 11: 8 Quick Solutions","url":"https://windowsreport.com/windows-11-no-sound/"},{"title":"c# - Playing Windows System Sounds with System.Media.SoundPlayer - Stack Overflow","url":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/22123899/playing-windows-system-sounds-with-system-media-soundplayer"},{"title":"How to Fix the Sound on Your Computer (Windows 10 & 11)","url":"https://www.avast.com/c-no-sound-on-computer"}]},"Based on the search results, here are the key troubleshooting steps for C# WPF SystemSounds not playing on Windows 11/10:\n\n## Windows System Settings to Check\n\nGo to Settings > System > Sound > Volume Mixer. Under apps > System Sounds - put slider at 100% and make sure there is no X through the little sound icon to the left that would denote system sounds are muted.(no content)Try making your sound scheme \"Windows Default\" to see if system sounds will then play.(no content)Make sure the mute setting is not turned on and try turning up all the volume controls. Note: Some speakers and apps have their own volume controls. Be sure to check them all.\n\n## Code-Related Issues\n\nCheck that your event handler was actually hooked up in your MainWindow.xaml to Button's click event, e.g.: `<Button Name=\"Button1\" Click=\"Button1_MouseLeftButtonDown\" />`(no content)WPF has a class called SoundPlayer, which will play audio content based on the WAV format for you. WAV is not a very widely used format today, mainly because it's uncompressed and therefore takes up a LOT of space\n\n## Additional Troubleshooting Steps\n\nSometimes having audio enhancements on can result in audio issues. Disabling them may resolve your issue.(no content)Select Start > Settings > Sound. In the Output section, select the audio device you're using (e.g., your speakers or headphones). On the page that opens, scroll to Advanced settings, then set Audio enhancements to Off from the dropdown menu.(no content)If multiple audio output devices are available, check that you have the appropriate one selected.(no content)Since the sound seems to be in a compressed format, it has to be decompressed before you can play it using SoundPlayer. You can use Windows Audio Compression Manager to decompress the sound for playback - though for SystemSounds this shouldn't typically be an issue.\n\n## Registry and Group Policy\n\nHave you checked the registry keys shown in the tutorial towards the end?(no content)Windows key + R, gpedit.msc opens the group policy editor. If any are set you may also see text in red in Settings \"Some settings are managed by....\"\n\n## Alternative Workarounds\n\nYou can change the sound scheme for Windows to \"No Sounds\", so even though it's not muted in the mixer, system sounds will not play. - This is the opposite of what you want, but indicates sound scheme settings are important.\n\nOne was fixed by creating a new user account. - This can help determine if it's a user-specific issue.\n\nThe most common causes are muted System Sounds in the Volume Mixer, incorrect sound scheme settings, or disabled audio enhancements interfering with playback."],"durationSeconds":31.101218899999978}}
